Claims What is claimed is: 1. A heat exchanger, comprising : (a) a first plate having an inner surface and an outer surface; (b) a second plate having an inner surface and an outer surface, wherein the first and second plates are joined together with their inner surfaces in opposed facing relation to one another, and with portions of the inner surfaces being spaced apart from one another; (c) a plurality of fluid flow passages adapted for flow of a heat transfer fluid, and located between the spaced apart portions of the inner surfaces of the first and second plates; (d) a dividing rib which separates the heat exchanger into an inlet section and an outlet section, each of the inlet section and the outlet section including a plurality of said fluid flow passages; (e) an inlet port located in the inlet section for supplying the heat transfer fluid to the plurality of fluid flow passages; and (e) an outlet port in the outlet section for discharging the heat transfer fluid from the plurality of fluid flow passages; wherein both the inlet port and the outlet port are located proximate to a first end of the heat exchanger, on opposite sides of the dividing rib; wherein the portions of the inner surfaces of the first and second plates which are spaced apart from one another define a total heat transfer surface area of the heat exchanger, and wherein the total heat transfer surface area is a sum of the heat transfer surface area of the inlet section and the heat transfer surface area of the outlet section; and 

 wherein the heat transfer surface area of the inlet section is less than the heat transfer surface area of the outlet section. 2. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein the inlet and outlet sections of the heat exchanger have substantially the same area. 3. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein dividing rib has a first end and a second end and extends along a central longitudinal axis of the heat exchanger, wherein the second end of the dividing rib is spaced from a second end of the heat exchanger to provide a gap through which flow communication is provided between the inlet section and the outlet section. 4. The heat exchanger according to claim 3, wherein the dividing rib extends along the central longitudinal axis. 5. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein the outer surface of the first plate is adapted for thermal contact with bottom surfaces of plurality of battery cells arranged in side-by-side relation along a central longitudinal axis of the heat exchanger; wherein the heat exchanger comprises a plurality of zones, each of the zones having an area corresponding to an area of the bottom surface of one of the battery cells; each of the zones having an inlet portion lying in the inlet section of the heat exchanger and an outlet portion lying in the outlet section of the heat exchanger; and each of the zones having a heat transfer surface area which is a portion of the total heat transfer surface area, with the heat transfer surface area of each of the zones being divided between the inlet section and the outlet section of the heat exchanger. 6. The heat exchanger according to claim 5, wherein one of the zones comprises a proximal zone which is immediately adjacent to the inlet and outlet ports at the first end of the heat exchanger, wherein the heat transfer surface area of the proximal zone is unevenly divided between the inlet and outlet sections of the heat exchanger, with a portion of the proximal zone heat transfer surface area lying in the outlet section being greater than a portion of the proximal zone heat transfer surface area lying in the inlet section. 7. The heat exchanger according to claim 6, wherein one of the zones comprises a distal zone which is proximate to a second end of the heat exchanger and farthest from the inlet and outlet ports; wherein the heat transfer surface area of the distal zone is evenly divided between the inlet and outlet sections of the heat exchanger. 8. The heat exchanger according to claim 6, wherein the plurality of zones includes at least one intermediate zone between the proximal zone and the distal zone. 9. The heat exchanger according to any one of claims 5 to 8, wherein one or more of said zones, including the proximal zone, has its heat transfer surface area unevenly divided between the inlet and outlet sections of the heat exchanger, with a portion of the heat transfer surface area lying in the outlet section being greater than a portion of the heat transfer surface area lying in the inlet section; and wherein the one or more of said zones have a total length which is about 10- 50 percent of the length of the heat exchanger. 10. The heat exchanger according to claim 9, wherein two or more of said zones have their heat transfer surface areas unevenly divided between the inlet and outlet sections, and wherein said two or more zones are contiguous. 11. The heat exchanger according to claim 9 or 10 wherein, in each of said zones having its heat transfer surface area unevenly divided between the inlet and outlet sections of the heat exchanger, the portion of the heat transfer surface area lying in the inlet section is about 10-80 percent smaller than the portion of the heat transfer surface area lying in the outlet section. 12. The heat exchanger according to claim 11, wherein the portion of the heat transfer surface area lying in the inlet section is about 25-60 percent smaller than the portion of the heat transfer surface area lying in the outlet section. 13. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein each of the zones has a length which is about 25 percent of the length of the heat exchanger, and a width which is about the same as a width of the heat exchanger. 14. The heat exchanger according to any one of claims 9 to 13, wherein each of the zones having its heat transfer surface area unevenly divided between the inlet and outlet sections of the heat exchanger has at least one flow obstruction provided in its inlet portion; wherein the one or more flow obstructions occupy from about 50-90 percent of the width of the inlet portion of the zone in which it is provided, and from about 50-90 percent of the length of the zone. 15. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein the inlet section includes one or more flow obstructions located between the inlet port and first ends of the plurality of fluid flow passages in the inlet section. 16. The heat exchanger according to claim 15, wherein each of the flow obstructions has a top sealing surface which is sealingly joined to the inner surface of the first plate. 17. The heat exchanger according to claim 16, wherein each of the flow obstructions comprises a dead channel including a continuous outer rib structure completely surrounding a depressed middle region. 18. The heat exchanger according to claim 17, wherein each of the flow obstructions has a pair of side edges, a leading edge and a trailing edge, all of which partly define regions of fluid flow, such that each of the flow obstructions is completely surrounded by said regions of fluid flow. 19. The heat exchanger according to claim 18, wherein the side edges of each said flow obstruction are parallel to each other and to the fluid flow passages in the inlet section. 20. The heat exchanger according to claim 18 or 19, wherein one or more ribs or dimples are provided between the inlet port and the flow obstruction. 21. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein a thickness of the first plate in a portion of the inlet section is greater than a thickness of the plate in the outlet section. 22. The heat exchanger according to claim 21, wherein the portion of greater thickness in the first plate is provided in an area of the inlet section which is proximate to the inlet port. 23. The heat exchanger according to claim 22, wherein the portion of greater thickness in the first plate is provided by a sheet of metal secured to the inner surface of the first plate. 24. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, wherein the heat exchanger is a cold plate adapted to support a plurality of battery cells on the outer surface of the first plate; wherein the inner and outer surfaces of the first plate are substantially flat; 

 wherein the second plate is a shaped plate having a generally flat, planar base surrounded by a raised peripheral sidewall extending from the base to a planar flange defining a planar peripheral sealing surface along which the inner surface of the second plate is sealingly joined to the inner surface of the first plate; wherein the dividing rib is formed in the second plate, and the second plate further comprises a plurality of channel ribs which define sides of the fluid flow passages; and wherein the dividing ribs and the channel ribs have top surfaces which are sealingly joined to the inner surface of the first plate. 25. The heat exchanger according to claim 1, further comprising a layer of thermal interface material is provided on the outer surface of the first plate.
